<section id="itsm_toolRef">
    <title>toolRef</title>
    
    <para>Tool Reference - the <code>toolRef</code> attribute is the <olink
            targetdoc="../xliff21.xml" targetptr="ITS20">[ITS]</olink> defined <code>toolRef</code>
        attribute.</para>
    
    
    <para><emphasis>Value description:</emphasis> IRI</para>
    <para>The IRI is supposed to resolve as human or machine readable <ulink
            url="https://www.w3.org/TR/its20/#provenanceDefs">Tool-related provenance
            information</ulink>.</para>
    
    <para><emphasis>Default value:</emphasis> default values for this attribute
        depend on the element in which it is used:</para>
    
    <itemizedlist>
        <listitem>
            <para>When used in any admissible element WITH the <olink targetdoc="itsm_provenanceRecordsRef.xml" targetptr="itsm_provenanceRecordsRef"><code>provenanceRecordsRef</code></olink> attribute set:</para>
            <para>The value of the <link linkend="itsm_toolRef"><code>toolRef</code></link> attribute
                of the first <olink targetdoc="../../elements/itsm/provenanceRecord.xml" targetptr="itsm_provenanceRecord"><code>&lt;provenanceRecord></code></olink> element with the <link linkend="itsm_toolRef"><code>toolRef</code></link> attribute set within the referenced <olink targetdoc="../../elements/itsm/provenanceRecords.xml" targetptr="itsm_provenanceRecords"><code>&lt;provenanceRecords></code></olink> element (which can be undefined).</para>
            
        </listitem>
        
        <listitem>
            <para>When used in any admissible element WITHOUT the <olink targetdoc="itsm_provenanceRecordsRef.xml" targetptr="itsm_provenanceRecordsRef"><code>provenanceRecordsRef</code></olink> attribute set:</para>
            <para>The default values depening on the element in which it is used:</para>
            
            
            <itemizedlist>
                <listitem>
                    <para>When used in <olink targetdoc="../../elements/structural/file.xml"
                        targetptr="file"><code>&lt;file&gt;</code></olink> or <olink
                            targetdoc="../../elements/itsm/provenanceRecord.xml" targetptr="revision"
                            ><code>&lt;its:provencanceRecord></code></olink>:</para>
                    
                    <para>The value is undefined.</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>When used in any other admissible structural element (<olink
                        targetdoc="../../elements/structural/group.xml" targetptr="group"
                        ><code>&lt;group></code></olink> or <olink
                            targetdoc="../../elements/structural/unit.xml" targetptr="unit"
                            ><code>&lt;unit></code></olink>):</para>
                    <para>The value of the <link linkend="itsm_toolRef"
                        ><code>toolRef</code></link> attribute of its parent element
                        (which can be undefined).</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>When used in annotations markers <olink targetdoc="../../elements/inline/mrk.xml"
                        targetptr="mrk"><code>&lt;mrk></code></olink> or <olink
                            targetdoc="../../elements/inline/sm.xml" targetptr="sm"
                            ><code>&lt;sm></code></olink>:</para>
                    <para>The value of the <link linkend="itsm_toolRef"
                            ><code>toolRef</code></link> attribute of the innermost <olink
                            targetdoc="../../elements/inline/mrk.xml" targetptr="mrk"
                                ><code>&lt;mrk></code></olink>, <olink
                            targetdoc="../../elements/structural/unit.xml" targetptr="unit"
                                ><code>&lt;unit&gt;</code></olink>, <olink
                            targetdoc="../../elements/candidates/match.xml" targetptr="match"
                                ><code>&lt;mtc:match></code></olink>, or <olink
                            targetdoc="../../elements/change-tracking/revision.xml"
                            targetptr="revision"
                        ><code>&lt;ctr:revision></code></olink><!-- relationship with the ctr:author atribute will be described in teh Provenance category spec <para>In the special case that the parent element of the marker is a <olink
                    targetdoc="../../elements/itms/revision.xml" targetptr="revision"
                        ><code>&lt;ctr:revision></code></olink> element, the value is need to be reflected in the value of the <olink targetdoc="../../attributes/change-tracking/ctr_author.xml"
                    targetptr="ctr_author"><code>ctr:author</code></olink> attribute of the parent
                    <olink targetdoc="../../elements/itms/revision.xml" targetptr="revision"
                        ><code>&lt;ctr:revision></code></olink> (which can be undefined ???).</para>-->
                        element, in which the marker in question is located (which can be
                        undefined).</para>
                </listitem>
                
            </itemizedlist>
        </listitem>
        
        
        
        
        
    </itemizedlist>
    
    
    
    <para><emphasis>Used in:</emphasis>
        <olink targetdoc="../../elements/structural/file.xml" targetptr="file"><code>&lt;file></code></olink>, <olink targetdoc="../../elements/structural/group.xml" targetptr="group"><code>&lt;goup></code></olink>, <olink targetdoc="../../elements/structural/unit.xml" targetptr="unit"><code>&lt;unit></code></olink>, 
        <olink targetdoc="../../elements/inline/mrk.xml" targetptr="mrk"
            ><code>&lt;mrk></code></olink>,
        <olink targetdoc="../../elements/inline/sm.xml"
            targetptr="sm"><code>&lt;sm></code></olink>, <olink targetdoc="../../elements/itsm/provenanceRecord.xml" targetptr="itsm_provenanceRecord"><code>&lt;provenanceRecord></code></olink>, <olink
                targetdoc="../../elements/candidates/match.xml" targetptr="match"
                ><code>&lt;mtc:match></code></olink>, and <olink
                    targetdoc="../../elements/itms/revision.xml" targetptr="revision"
                    ><code>&lt;ctr:revision></code></olink>.
    </para>
    
    
    <para>See the <olink targetdoc="../../modules/itsm/Provenance.xml" targetptr="provenanceAnnotation">ITS Provenance Annotation</olink> for the normative usage description of this attribute on inline elements. Advanced Constraints follow from that normative usage description.</para>
    
</section>
